The contract source confirms the core issue: `selfSwap()` is public, `fill()` does `router.call(routerData)` as Dexible, and `tokenOut.amount = 0` is valid. The main constraint is fee settlement: if `feeToken == tokenIn`, Dexible later pulls protocol fees from the caller via `safeTransferFrom`, so the verifier needs some allowed fee-token balance or it has to use an output-fee flow that leaves Dexible holding the stolen token first.
